Package com.phonytive.astive.agi.command

Class Summary
Answer Answers channel if not already in answer state.
AsyncAgiBreak Interrupts expected flow of Async AGI commands and returns control to previous source (typically, the PBX dialplan).
ControlStreamFile Send the given file, allowing playback to be controlled by the given digits, if any.
DatabaseDel Deletes an entry in the Asterisk database for a given family and key
DatabaseDelTree Deletes a family or specific keytree within a family in the Asterisk database.
DatabaseGet Retrieves an entry in the Asterisk database for a given family and key
DatabasePut Adds or updates an entry in the Asterisk database for a given family>, key, value
Exec Executes application with given options.
GetChannelStatus Returns the status of the specified channel.
GetData Stream the given file, and receive DTMF data.
GetFullVariable Returns 0 if variablename is not set or channel does not exist.
GetOption Behaves similar to StreamFile but used with a timeout option.
GetVariable Returns 0 if variablename is not set.
GoSub Cause the channel to execute the specified dialplan subroutine, returning to the dialplan with execution of a Return().
Hangup Hangs up the specified channel.
Noop Does nothing.
ReceiveChar Receives a character of text on a channel.
ReceiveText Receives a string of text on a channel.
RecordFile Record to a file until a given DTMF digit in the sequence is received.
SayAlpha Say a given character string, returning early if any of the given DTMF digits are received on the channel.
SayDate Say a given date, returning early if any of the given DTMF digits are received on the channel.
SayDatetime Say a given time, returning early if any of the given DTMF digits are received on the channel.
SayDigits Say a given digit string, returning early if any of the given DTMF digits are received on the channel.
SayNumber Say a given number, returning early if any of the given DTMF digits are received on the channel.
SayPhonetic Say a given character string with phonetics, returning early if any of the given DTMF digits are received on the channel.
SayTime Say a given time, returning early if any of the given DTMF digits are received on the channel
SendImage Sends the given image on a channel.
SendText Sends the given text on a channel.
SetAutoHangup Cause the channel to automatically hangup at time seconds in the future.
SetCallerId Changes the callerid of the current channel.
SetContext Sets the context for continuation upon exiting the application.
SetExtension Changes the extension for continuation upon exiting the application.
SetMusic Enables/Disables the music on hold generator.
SetPriority Changes the priority for continuation upon exiting the application.
SetVariable Sets a variable to the current channel.
SpeechActivateGrammar Activates the specified grammar on the speech object.
SpeechCreate Create a speech object to be used by the other Speech AGI commands.
SpeechDeactivateGrammar Deactivates the specified grammar on the speech object.
SpeechDestroy Destroy the speech object created by SpeechCreate.
SpeechLoadGrammar Unloads the specified grammar.
SpeechRecognize Plays back given prompt while listening for speech and DTMF.
SpeechSet Set an engine-specific setting in a key/value format.
SpeechUnloadGrammar Unloads the specified grammar.
StreamFile Send the given file, allowing playback to be interrupted by the given digits, if any.
TddMode Enable/Disable TDD transmission/reception on a channel.
Verbose Sends message to the console via verbose message system.
WaitForDigit Waits up to timeout milliseconds for channel to receive a DTMF digit.
